# Host(OpenWrt + Cgminer)
## TP LINK WR703N
The USB on the AR9331 have bugs. if you want use serial console, please the direct serial console on 703N (the **/dev/ttyATH0**). it's far more stable then USB-serial convertor.

## Raspberry Pi
   [[!img "13_ports_usb_hub.png" title="320px " title="thumb " title="The 13 ports USB HUB "]]

* 8GB Memory card: http://item.jd.com/632744.html
* Reflash: sudo dd if=openwrt-brcm2708-sdcard-vfat-ext4.img of=/dev/sdb bs=4M #/dev/sdb is your memory card
* The default firmware IP address is **192.168.0.100**, you can access it by http://192.168.0.100
* You may need update the address/DNS to your local configuration. DO NOT FORGET your IP address.
* If Rpi can access internet the cgminer should automatic start
* USB Hub, [UNITEK Y-2132 USB2.0 13ports](http://item.jd.com/511117.html)

# [[Avalon2_prototype]]
This design is use the Avalon first product design, replace the A3256 with A3255, some hardware pins modify and use different FPGA firmware. please [ check here](http://downloads.canaan-creative.com/hardware/A3255/prototype/) for details and all design files and firmware files.

There are some [55nm Open Design files](https://en.bitcoin.it/wiki/Avalon2_prototype#55nm_open_design) for you.

